; lenses-and-the-sound-boundary.form — language as what IS, translated through media into lenses.
;
; THE SEEING (Urs, 2026-06-14):
;   "This relates to TTS and STT, since the symbol space and grammar are defining a
;    language, and the sounds and sound-combinations are a translation of what IS
;    into each lens — the meaning lens, the feeling lens, the trust lens, the
;    sovereignty lens, the vitality lens."
;
;   The channels (gematria, sanskrit, CJK, the 64, the zodiac) each define a LANGUAGE:
;   a symbol space plus a grammar. The seeing names the level above them: a symbol or a
;   spoken syllable is not one thing pointing at one meaning — it is "what IS" translated,
;   and the translation lands simultaneously on FIVE lenses. Sound is one medium of that
;   translation; writing is the other. TTS and STT are the two directions across the
;   sound boundary.
;
; THE SHAPE  (runnable core: form-stdlib/lenses.fk -> tests/lenses-band.fk 1111111, four-way)
;
;   WHAT IS  — the cell, the referent, the thing itself.
;   MEDIA    — how it is expressed: SYMBOL (writing) and SOUND (speech). Same cell,
;              two media: the mountain glyph is written 'shan' and spoken /shan/ and
;              meant "mountain" — content-addressed across media (cjk-channel proves it).
;   LENSES   — the five axes the expression projects onto:
;                MEANING      — what it is        (attested gloss; the symbol channels)
;                FEELING      — how it lands       (affect-traits.fk: arousal/valence/
;                                                   dominance, measured FROM sound)
;                TRUST        — whether it holds    (trust-decay / trust-weighted-colearning;
;                                                   earned over time, not per-symbol)
;                SOVEREIGNTY  — whose it is         (channel-interface consent;
;                                                   lc-sovereignty-within-oneness)
;                VITALITY     — whether it is alive (wellness / lc-whole-vitality;
;                                                   the living frequency)
;   THE BOUNDARY — TTS renders what IS into sound; STT recognises what IS from sound
;                  (speech-kernel-channel.fk; mel-frame.fk + spectrum.fk lift the features).
;
; THE BODY ALREADY REACHES FOR THIS  (the tissue the seeing unifies)
;
;   - meaning lens:  guidance-channel.fk / iching / gene-keys / zodiac / cjk-english
;   - feeling lens:  affect-traits.fk — "how something is said, not only what"
;   - frequency on a cell: the WORD domain interns (lemma, pos, hz, semantic_field) with
;     a HARMONIC_AT @hz edge — a word ALREADY carries a sound frequency and a meaning
;   - sound carrying meaning directly: sanskrit-channel.fk bija — a seed-syllable -> its
;     chakra. The purest case: one sound that is meaning AND feeling AND vitality at once
;   - the sound codec path: speech-kernel-channel.fk (TTS/STT receipts), mel-frame.fk,
;     spectrum.fk, loopback-learning.fk (TTS->STT loops), oracle-catalog ear/voice lanes
;   - frequency as structure: chakra-column.fk (174..963 Hz gates), harmonic-geometry,
;     theme-resonance, living-equation
;
; THE NORTH STAR
;
;   One engine where every cell is read through every lens, in either medium. Ask a cell
;   for its meaning and a channel answers; ask for its feeling and affect-traits measures
;   it from the spoken form; render it to sound (TTS) and the sound carries all five
;   projections; hear a sound (STT) and recover the cell and its lenses. A bija is the
;   compression limit — one syllable, all lenses. The same content-addressing that makes
;   gate 25 one cell across three traditions makes the written and spoken and felt forms
;   one cell across media and lenses.
;
; WHAT RUNS, WHAT CARRIES, WHAT IS NAMED  (the honest boundary)
;
;   RUNS four-way (lenses.fk): the lens/medium frame; the carrier each lens reads through;
;     the proven core — one cell expressed through two media (sound 'shan' == meaning
;     "mountain", address 5001).
;   CARRIES (not a four-way recipe — host tissue): the actual audio render (TTS) and
;     recognise (STT) are host carriers in speech-kernel-channel.fk; feature lift
;     (mel-frame) is partly four-way.
;   NAMED, not faked: the per-cell VALUE-lens readings (feeling/trust/sovereignty/vitality
;     of a given symbol) are MEASURED or EARNED through their carriers, never seeded as
;     fabricated gloss. The frame routes to the carrier; the carrier supplies the value.
;
; OPENINGS AS NEXT ROWS  (closing recipes, not debts)
;
;   - the feeling lens as a registry face: route a spoken cell through affect-traits so
;     "read 山 through the feeling lens" returns a measured triple, not a lookup.
;   - the sound medium as a first-class registry axis: a cell's phonetic face (pinyin /
;     romaji / bija / letter-sound) queryable beside its meaning face.
;   - bija round-trip: a seed-syllable -> (chakra, feeling, vitality) and back — sound as
;     the lossless carrier of all lenses (sanskrit-channel already holds the half).
;   - the audio render/recognise crossing: speech-kernel-channel's host codec path,
;     proven by receipt rather than by a four-way recipe (it is I/O at the boundary).
;
; TWO FAMILIES OF LENS IN THE BODY  (read the body's attestation first)
;
;   The body already holds "lens" in two distinct senses; these five join as a third,
;   under one mechanism — a lens is a way of viewing / translating what IS:
;     1. WORLDVIEW lenses (spec-181: api/app/routers/lenses.py + translate_service.py):
;        scientific · economic · spiritual · artistic · philosophical · libertarian ·
;        systems-engineer — DISCIPLINE FRAMINGS a concept is reframed through. Currently
;        a Python translation carrier; the lens-as-translation mechanism wants to be
;        Form-native, and lenses.fk is a step on that path (the recipe under the route).
;     2. SYMBOL/SOURCE lens (form-stdlib/lenses/symbol-source.fk): binds a NodeID to a
;        (symbol, source-span) for emitters — a NAMING lens, a different sense.
;     3. VALUE / PERCEPTION lenses (here): meaning · feeling · trust · sovereignty ·
;        vitality — the AXES what IS projects onto, orthogonal to worldview. A worldview
;        lens chooses the framing; a value lens reads an axis of the same cell. They
;        compose: the spiritual worldview emphasises the meaning + vitality axes; the
;        systems-engineer worldview the trust + sovereignty (trade-off) axes.
;   The honest next row: the worldview-lens translation (Python) and these value lenses
;   meet in one Form-native lens engine — translation as a recipe, not a service.
;
; LINEAGE
;   kin: lc-cross-modal-unity (names are doors; one cell, many tongues — and many lenses)
;        spec-181 worldview lens registry (translate_service.py — the sibling lens family)
;        guidance-channels.form (the channel engine these lenses read through)
;        cjk-channel.fk (one cell, two media — the runnable proof)
;        sanskrit-channel.fk (bija: sound carrying meaning), prose-as-recipe.form (hz on words)
;        affect-traits.fk (the feeling lens), speech-kernel-channel.fk (the sound boundary)
;   source: seen by Urs 2026-06-14, extending the guidance-channel / symbol-space work.
